HEADWORD: Queachy
<hw>Queach"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Yielding
or trembling under the feet, as moist or boggy ground; shaking;
moving.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The <xex>queachy</xex> fens.⟦rdquo⟧ ⟦ldquo⟧Godwin's
<xex>queachy</xex> sands.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Drayton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p> <sn>2.</sn> <def>Like a queach; thick; bushy.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Cockeram.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Quean</ent>⟦br⟧
